      <div class="slds-col">
        <div class="slds-text-heading_large slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          duplicate Manager Help
        </div>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-var-p-bottom_small">
          Overview
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          The duplicate Manager is a tool for identifying, analyzing, and
          merging duplicate records in Salesforce. It provides advanced
          capabilities beyond Salesforce's native duplicate management features.
        </p>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-var-p-bottom_small">
          Key Features
        </div>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Configuration-based duplicate identification across objects</li>
          <li>Batch processing for large volume of records</li>
          <li>Interactive side-by-side record comparison</li>
          <li>Field-level merge decisions</li>
          <li>Scheduled job management</li>
          <li>Detailed statistics and reporting</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-var-p-bottom_small">
          Using the duplicate Manager
        </div>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_small slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Dashboard
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          The Dashboard provides an overview of duplicate statistics, including
          duplicates found and records merged. It offers filtering by object
          type and time range.
        </p>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_small slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Batch Jobs
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">Use the Batch Jobs tab to:</p>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Run "dry run" analyses to find duplicates without merging</li>
          <li>Execute merge operations</li>
          <li>View job progress</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_small slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Compare
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          The Compare tab shows a side-by-side view of potential duplicates,
          allowing you to:
        </p>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Select the master record</li>
          <li>Choose field values from specific records</li>
          <li>Preview the merge result</li>
          <li>Confirm the merge operation</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_small slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Scheduled Jobs
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          Manage scheduled duplicate detection and merge jobs:
        </p>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Create recurring jobs</li>
          <li>View scheduled job status</li>
          <li>Modify or delete scheduled jobs</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_small slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Audit Logs
        </div>
        <p class="slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          Review historical merge operations with detailed logs showing:
        </p>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Master record information</li>
          <li>Merged record IDs</li>
          <li>Field-level merge decisions</li>
          <li>User who performed the merge</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Best Practices
        </div>
        <ul class="slds-list_dotted slds-var-p-bottom_medium">
          <li>Always run a dry run analysis before merging records</li>
          <li>Schedule large merge jobs during off-peak hours</li>
          <li>Regularly review audit logs to verify merge operations</li>
          <li>Use field-level merge decisions for critical data</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="slds-text-heading_medium slds-var-p-vertical_small">
          Need More Help?
        </div>
        <p>
          Contact your system administrator for additional support or
          configuration assistance.
        </p>
      </div>
